description: The annual journal Dumbarton Oaks Papers was founded in 1941 for the publication of articles relating to late antique, early medieval, and Byzantine civilization in the fields of art and architecture, history, archeology, literature, theology, law, and the auxiliary disciplines. Numerous maps, tables, illustrations, and color plates provide supplementary information for many of the articles.Dumbarton Oaks Papers 53 (1999) Dumbarton Oaks Papers 54 (2000) Dumbarton Oaks Papers 55 (2001) Dumbarton Oaks Papers 56 (2002)Dumbarton Oaks Papers 57 (2003)
